==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stipple
<hw>Stip"ple</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Stippled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Stippling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[D.
<ets>stippelen</ets> to make points, to spot, dot, from
<ets>stippel</ets>, dim. of <ets>stip</ets> a dot, spot.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To engrave by means of dots, in distinction from
engraving in lines.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The interlaying of small pieces can not altogether avoid a broken,
<qex>stippled</qex>, spotty effect.</q> <rj><qau>Milman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To paint, as in water colors, by small, short
touches which together produce an even or softly graded
surface.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stippling</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Stipple</ent>⟦br⟧
